# idocvident — team standards

## Project

- Next.js 16 App Router app with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and ESLint
- Source lives under `src/`; pages and layouts under `src/app/`
- Project name: **idocvident**

## How we work

- Keep changes focused; avoid unrelated refactors in the same PR
- Run `npm run lint` before opening a PR
- Prefer small, reviewable commits with clear messages
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, credentials)

## Agent behavior

- Read existing code before adding new patterns
- Match naming, imports, and file layout already in the repo
- For Next.js APIs, check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` when unsure — this template may differ from older Next.js versions
- Ask before large architectural changes or new dependencies

## Collaboration

- Pull latest `main` before starting work: `git pull origin main`
- Use feature branches: `git checkout -b feature/short-description`
- Open a PR for review; do not push directly to `main` once teammates are active
